Now called Sidecar. Very good service, great food.
Great meal!  The Chilean Sea Bass was excellent!
Great food & cocktails
The oysters are always on point!
This is my favorite place in Frederick.
Would absolutely recommend trying out this place. Exceptional ambience, flavorful food, fantastic customer service. I recommend this place.

What a bad experience! I was showing downtown Frederick to my friend who was visiting. After we ate lunch, we dropped by Raw Bar to get some raw oysters. We ordered two each of all three different kinds they offered to start out. Half of the oysters had barely nothing in it. See attached. I showed the waiter and he said “They are oysters.”  Then he stared at me with intimidating look. He was very rude and showed no effort to make us happy. I asked if there’s anything he can do about it, and he turned back to the kitchen and brought the replacement in silence. No apology whatsoever. We thanked him and left. What a disappointment. We were wondering how he would’ve treated us if we were not two asian females. We also noticed that he was waring a face shield without a mask, which is proven to be not as effective, and how it complies the safety guidelines.
Omgosh!!  Love this place .  The food is Divine as well as presentation. The staff are well chosen, all smart n kind,  present well, make good suggestions and r  most worthy of generous tips !

Went to Firestone's Raw Bar in Frederick on 18 July. This is the third time I have been there and the first since COVID. All three times the variety of oysters has been exceptional.  I went yesterday with some good friends as a form of farewell and the 3 dozen oysters we had were awesome, especially the Prince Edward Island oysters.  They were much smaller than the James River and other oyster species but had awesome flavor and brine. Having 3 dozen oysters will set you back by about $100 but sometimes you have to splurge. Overall fantastic eats, service was prompt and courteous and a memorable time with my favorite Frederick Familia.

Food and atmosphere were wonderful. Got the chefs tower, every thing was delicious. Gave it 4 stars because the service a bit dicey. We had to ask for our drinks, napkins, and silverware. The menu said that the chefs tower came with 21 oysters, they brought us 18 and when we noticed they brought us the last 3. Would definitely come back.
I eat here a lot since I work in the area. I like how the customer service is always awesome and they keep the place clean at all times. Pricing is reasonable and they serve big portions.
Best raw oysters in town!!!
Awesome restaurant, great oysters!
We had a wonderful time at this spot. We loved the excellent atmosphere and the food. The staff members were super personal. I’m happy we ultimately decided to eat here.

We were impressed with the great rating and decided to give it a try. Came for lunch on 01/19/2020 and sat at the bar. Rockfish ceviche was pretty good, oysters and wagyu carpaccio were ok. Lobster Bisque was pretty bad and we sent it back. But the worst part was when we saw how the bartender is preparing cheese platter and carpaccio. She used no gloves, just periodically wiped hands on her apron. Bartenders who constantly deal with money, wipe counter, etc. cannot prepare a raw food without gloves. It is not hygienic.
Wierd. Food is as you can immagine raw and wierd. Place smells like a firestone tire store.
Delicious!
Great food,awesome service.

Great place! Food is fantastic, go to Happy Hour for oyster specials so worth it, fresh and big. Meat/cheese boards yummy get a recommendation from server, especially for cheese. Martinis and other specialty drinks yummy.

One thing u need to get here. PASTRAMI. In their breakfast bowl. So good. They make it there. Also good - their cheese board, fried oyster samich, and they have a jazz band play sunday mornings. Also great staff
Nice atmosphere. Some unique and delicious menu items. May be considered a bit pricy, but not outrageous. Staff are friendly!
Food is fabulous!!!
I love this place. Always consistent, fresh and delicious with impeccable unobtrusive service. You can never go wrong with the seasonal ceviche or the oyster selections.
Oysters and crab was delicious. Had a bad tomato in the salad which turned me off. But all in all it's an ok spot.
Great place. Bit pricey.
Gem in downtown Frederick
Jackie at the Raw Bar is a hard worker and provided excellent customer service!!
Great sandwich the Tuscan chicken
Truly gourmet food for low prices. Great service and ambiance too.
Excellent service and food, and the drinks are delish.
Probably one of the best meals I've had on awhile. The oysters were fantastic and cheap with the happy hour deal. Definitely would recommend!
Great oysters. Decent Prices. The ambiance is decent too
Try the spicy margarita!
Great food, great atmosphere

I loved my dinner here so much. One of the best seafood restaurants for me, and I'm very picky about my seafood. Everything was fresh, flavorful and prepared perfectly. My party of 4 shared and sampled several dishes, all of which I would recommend. Beef tartar, oysters, chicken liver mousse, poke bowl, seared scallops with mushroom risotto, soft shell crabs, and bread pudding were all divine. I literally wanted to try the entire menu. So wish this restaurant was closer to where I live.
Incredible high-end food. Oysters are delicious and sides are perfect. Their meat and cheese platter is to die for.
My favorite raw bar!!

Really nice. I have been there many times.  Service isn't always consistent, but never bad.  Had the tower and was more than enough for two people.  I enjoy sitting at the street window and watch the downtown people!
I had a good experience. Food was good. I wish it came with more food though. I had the oysters,shrimp cocktail,duck sausage and a margarita
For the price will return anytime to enjoy the experience...
Steak tartare with fair...

what a wonderful menu..our second time here and the food was prepared perfectly...raw bar oysters 3 from Maryland 3 from Virginia were so tasty!  Great service at the bar. Prices wwre acceptable for the amount and the quality of the food.

Great atmosphere and service! The raw bar oysters were amazing, as was the rockfish cerviche. We wanted to try everything that the waiters walked by when because of how good it smelled and looked. Great prices too. Definitely will return.
Amazing oysters. Absolutely loved the truffle honey and charcuterie/cheese board. Great happy hour deals
They short-change; screw them.
Love this place! The chefs board is amazing and the variety of oysters is great. Also, our waiter, whose name I missed so I'll just call him Norm McD, was awesome.
Super delicious and creative flavors!
Food is fantastic!
raw Oyster lovers must visit
I had a half dozen oysters and the cerviche. The oysters we're tasty and well presented and the cerviche was excellent. The service was also very good.

I consider this one of my favorite places to dine. Always excellent food and service. Getting a seat by the window is a plus.
Food was good. Service was slow. Arrived at 11am, Sunday, got food about 1245, that's too slow for me.
Indulgent, and worth every bite
Excellent place. Excellent food. Excellent service. Steamed mussels were the best we ever had and their broth made us order extra bread.
This is the best restaurant in Frederick. From the food to the beer to the service, Raw Bar is amazing! We absolutely love it, and sneak away there anytime we can!
Love this place..awesome food and drink, great service.
Delicious octopus and lentil salad! Good service and good food!
Top quality seafood. European style dishes, so be ready for a chef-is-king style of dining. Pescatarian heaven, not much for more strict veggies.
Absolutely amazing food, at a reasonable price!!! Alice was an awesome server, never pressing us in our dinner experience. If you're in Frederick, you must visit Firestone's!!!
Raw oysters, unique tasty foods. Yum
Prices, portions, and service were great. We really enjoyed the oysters and cheese plate. Highly recommend :)
Great service, great oysters, best raw bar in town!
Raw bar is phenomenal

The experience was terrible. Hoping for an early dinner we requested a table for six at 3:30. They said they had a limited menu and limited seating until 5:00 and told us to come back at that time when their upstairs seating opened. When we returned they said they couldn't accommodate us even though there was no one in the entry area, few people at the bar and downstairs seating area and NO ONE at all in the upstairs area. Not sure what the food tastes like but would recommend one of the many other options within walking distance.
Great oysters but the other menu items are well worth it. Staff is incredibly friendly. Sit at the bar if you can.
Great food: presentation, flavor, amount. Perfect. Chic, but comfortable decor. Pleasant staff.
So much fun.  The chef's board was awesome, lots of food.  Staff is attentive and was able to help with choices.  Wine list was good,  husband was pleased with beer selection, too
Love this place, Chef's Board is amazing, Oysters are straight out the Atlantic. Highly recommended....

Love Love Love this place! Never bad experience! More upscale feel, but still can wear jeans and dress casual. Food is superb! Service overall has been good, but can be hit or miss. Service at the bar seems quicker than at table. Oysters, Foi gras,  literally everything is on point! Had a Rockfish entree few months back that was to die for! Bit pricey for the portion but worth it. Drinks not a large selection but still decent, you will have some variety.
Excellent service, great happy hours. I love chef's choice oyster Thursdays, it's a great way to get to know oysters.
Awesome cocktails and delicious raw oysters! We really enjoyed our night.
Great happy hour specials. The scallops were to die for!
Nice little place. Not big on seafood, so can't speak to the food. Service was great, others liked the oysters. Well worth a look if you like fancy and seafood.
Yum!!!!!! And empty and still friendly on a Friday night at 10pm!
Great oysters but do not overlook the other delicious food and cocktails on the menu. Everything is excellent, including the service and the staff is very nice.
The oysters were fresh and awesome. The tuna tartare was fantastic as well. The service was great. Will definitely be back.
Great oysters, very fresh. Tuna tartar and service were very good. Liked the cocktail menu and the atmosphere.
Awesome food, inexperienced service
Great space and great food.  Had oysters, cured salmon, and pâté.  Wonderful addition to the downtown!
